claim.claim-text:
1. A wiring layer structure connected to a first electrode of a ferroelectric capacitor having first and second electrodes, comprising a main wiring layer and a coating layer on the outer periphery of this main wiring layer; 
wherein said main wiring layer comprises a first material that reacts with a substance that infiltrates from the outside to this main wiring layer and produces a reducing agent; and 
wherein said coating layer comprises a second material that is conductive and prevents infiltration into said main wiring layer of said substance.
